[]: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by ElMariachi &raquo; Sun Oct 20, 2013 6:34 pm @ monitoradiation : what I&#39;m trying to say is that unrelated to Shinji&#39;s choices and apparent free will, in the end his choices didn&#39;t had any consequences but the one planned by obscures forces unknown to him&#40;i.e. Gendo&#41;, be it by manipulating him to maximize the chances of him doing what Gendo wants. Tthat&#39;s why he paraded an half-dead Rei to make him pilot, and brought them close so Shinji would do everything,even die, to save her, triggering EVA-01&#39;s awakening, and 14 years later by sending Rei Q with Mark.09 to retrieve Shinji, betting that he will think that it&#39;s poka Rei with EVA-00 rescuing him from this den of madman that is the Wunder, and finally crushing him under the guilt of what happened to the world and the fact he didn&#39;t saved Rei to make him obsessed to find a way to atone to the point of complete delusion, which will make him pull out the spears. And if he refuses to do any of that? Brainwashing. To retake your metaphor, a more accurate one would be that your friends suggests you to watch 3.33 on Sunday by telling you that watching animes the Sunday is better because you are more rested than during the week... but if you decide that you&#39;ll wait Monday to see it at the anime club, then they will tie you to a chair and force you to see it the Sunday, even if you didn&#39;t know that you&#39;ll be forced to see it the Sunday when you made the choice to wait the Monday, in the end you still saw it the Sunday. That&#39;s exactly how Shinji&#39;s situation really was though the three first movies, the only moment where he really had a choice was when in Lilith&#39;s Chamber when Asuka ended out of battery and he cut off Kaworu&#39;s commands... and that&#39;s probably why Gendo was so overkill in breaking his son&#39;s mind to maximize the chances of him choosing to still make the gamble of pull out the spears even when Kaworu noticed that it was a trap and was begging him to stop. So in the end Shinji&#39;s freedom of choice was only an illusion, since whatever he choses, the choice will be imposed to him if it doesn&#39;t suit Gendo&#39;s plan. In the end, Shinji was a slave to Gendo, indeed ignorant of his condition, but a slave nonetheless. And that&#39;s why I&#39;m saying that Misato giving a choice to Shinji without trying to manipulate him into choosing a certain path and forcing him to take the one which is more convenient for her would be a very powerful symbol for FINAL, and definitively and unambiguously set WILLE as the good guys. Besides Misato was already doing that as soon as in 1.0 : when she brought him to Lilith&#39;s Chamber so Shinji would see that even the other people at NERV are risking their lives in this war, it was just so Shinji had all the informations before making his choice&#40;something no one else did&#41;, and she was still saying that she will accept whatever decision he will make. That&#39;s why she thanked him from the bottom of her heart later when he accepted to participate in operation Yashima. Sure Shinji actually didn&#39;t had a choice, since Gendo would had forced him pilot anyway via brainwashing, but neither Misato nor Shinji knew that, meaning that Misato&#39;s acceptance of whatever decision Shinji would have taken were genuine, and now in FINAL she is in a position to give him a real choice without someone behind the curtain ready to impose his will to him if he doesn&#39;t chose &quot;correctly&quot;. And no, I don&#39;t think that she will magnum his face when he comes back in FINAL : she clearly was worried for him when 4I was happening and the Wunder failed to stop EVA-13&#40;meaning that Shinji will die due to the DSS Choker&#41;, and besides in this post-apocalyptic world there is absolutely nothing else where Shinji could hide, so if Misato really decides to kill Shinji, he wouldn&#39;t have any chance of surviving, and I don&#39;t see Anno killing off meaninglessly the main protagonist like that! After all by the master&#39;s own admission Rebuild is Shinji&#39;s story!&#40;even if he admitted that he wanted to tell a &quot;Tale&quot; for Rebuild, the main POV through which we&#39;re seeing the events unfolding is Shinji&#39;s&#41;

