[]: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by ElMariachi &raquo; Mon Oct 21, 2013 4:06 am I see, now it boils down to see if Anno considers compatibilism as something... well, compatible with the Evangelion setting. Sure Shinj&#39;s decisions to pilot to spare Rei the burden to do it when she was half dead, to stay and fight Ramiel and the subsequent Angel, as well as trying to save Rei from Zeruel were still important and meaningful since they were genuine, but what I&#39;m saying is that his &quot;destiny&quot; wasn&#39;t in his hand, because there always was his father&#39;s shadow stirring him toward a certain decision&#40;which thankfully could be considered as heroic, until the moment it ended in EVA-01 awakening and wrecking Tokyo-3 and later to fell in a trap with the two spears&#41; and even was ready to force it out of him if Shinji decides something else. And I think that Anno doesn&#39;t think that compatibilism is a good thing, since WILLE, the good guys, are fighting Gendo and SEELE to let mankind decide of their own destiny instead of having it imposed to them. After all having humanity decide that staying in the form of Lilin is better than evolving into another lifeform through the HIP is nice and all, but if in the end SEELE still bring HIP and the forced evolution to their face and evolve them whether mankind want it or not, in the end the Lilin choice loose it&#39;s significance. And that trend was also present in EoE : Instrumentality happens, is forced through mankind via Shinji, but in the end he realize that Instrumentality is not what he want and proceed to break it to be back in the world of AT Fields and take his destiny on his own hands.&#40;sure that leave the plot hole that maybe some people found Instrumentality to be very enjoyable and wanted to stay, but I&#39;m no sure Anno thought about it, maybe the Rebuild was a way to fix that hole&#41; A compatibilist situation would be that Shinji get his epiphany, realize that actually his time as a being with an AT Field wasn&#39;t so bad because his feelings then were real and accept that fact... but can&#39;t do anything about it since he won&#39;t get out of Instrumentality. Evangelion is partly a coming of age story, and one big part of growing-up is to make you own decisions and build your own path, Shinji can make his own decision&#40;up until the end of 3.0 at least, but I&#39;m sure he will recover enough will in FINAL&#41;, now he needs to be able to forge his own path, something impossible before with Gendo carving his path for him&#40;even though Shinji didn&#39;t knew that&#41;, and that was even the case in 3.0 : Mark.09 would had made him come with her, willingly or not, and Gendo would had made him pilot with Kaworu, willingly or by using coercion. And Misato was very honest with Shinji even in 3.33, even with the &quot;Rei doesn&#39;t exist anymore&quot; comment, it&#39;s just that Mark.09 appeared before she could explain everything to him. I can&#39;t see her being cryptic just for the sake of it, it&#39;s possible that she wanted to manage a little Shinji instead of directly dropping the bomb that his actions 14 years basically changed Rei&#39;s prison from Zeruel&#39;s core to EVA-01&#39;s, and there was a lot of other things to discuss with him : like the fact that he&#39;s not in NERV but in WILLE, that they fight Gendo who is an enemy of mankind and actually always was, that Rei was one of many clones of his mother&#40;if they know that bit about Rei&#39;s &quot;donor&quot;&#41;, that the world is now a giant toxic ruin and that apparently he had an hand in it, for what exactly he&#39;s being punished&#40;which ties with the previous point&#41;... that makes a lot of things to explain in a very short time, and info-dumping him on one go would just make him believe that she lost her mind and/or is trying to trick him with some insane story... which is exactly what he believed when she desperately tried to convince him to stay with them when Mark.09 appeared. Finally, it&#39;s very ambiguous if Misato was the one who detonated the DSS Choker at the end of the movie, remember that it started to glow before the Wunder rammed EVA-13. The most logical think is that it activated automatically once EVA-13 awakened&#40;one if its functions is called &quot;Awakening Analysis Mode&quot;&#41;. It&#39;s possible that Misato hoped that by dragging EVA-13 far enough of the Door of Guf with the Wunder&#39;s AT Field cage and damaging it enough with main canons, the Eva will deactivate and 4I stops, which will allow for Shinji&#39;s life to be spared. But the plan was thwarted by Mark.09 damaging and hacking the ship, letting EVA-13 escape and resumes its position at the center of the Door, hence Misato knowing that now the only thing that can stop EVA-13 and 4I is the DSS Choker killing the pilot&#40;apparently she didn&#39;t know that Shinji wasn&#39;t the one wearing ti anymore&#41; And being sad or worried isn&#39;t the point here, the point is that this scene, alongside the one in which she couldn&#39;t detonate the Choker, serves to show that under that cold exterior, she still has feelings toward Shinji and want to prevent as much as possible to have to kill him. That would be weird to have her wanting to kill him on the spot in FINAL after that! Besides seeing Shinji&#39;s situation, WILLE and the Lilin is the only place he can go now, so if Misato wants him dead, nothing will be able to save Shinji from that, and having the main characters&#39; head be blown off at the beginning of the final movie will makes the rest of his story kinda moot, no? Besides the preview explicitly said that Shinji will find hope again in the place he ends up, hard to find hope when the person you considers as a mother wants your head, no? monitoradiation wrote: Thinking about this - it might be that there&#39;s a reason why they have to keep a BM alive - It could be that Shinji&#39;s soul will automatically return to the template within Eva-01 and his presence will make it impossible for Wille to use Eva-01 as an energy source. That&#39;s why they don&#39;t kill him. They need him out of Eva-01.

