[]: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by Stillborn &raquo; Mon Oct 21, 2013 5:52 am It would not be strange. I said before, Anno is playing god, and treats Evangelion as a Bible. Fills it with cryptic messages and symbols, tortures the characters for the sake of some &quot;message&quot; and gives often contradictive signals. So it would NOT be surprising nor unusual for me. It does not help Shinji grow up or evolve. It forces him to a certain path with karmic kicks, by stacking absurd amount of situational odds that points in only one &quot;proper&quot; direction. But we don&#39;t see humans directly forcing it, so it gives an illusion of choice. In reality, it forces Shinji into certain box without posiibility of flexibility. Everything he do will have bad outcome unless it follows exact karmic path, to a single designed &quot;proper&quot; outcome. I call this way of &quot;character developement&quot; hollow.

